row-level status across all available Enterococcus measurements on that date.\n# A row meets standards only if every available paired measurement is a non-violation.\ndef row_meets(row):\n    results = []\n    for tag_col, ent_col in ordered_pairs:\n        status = parse_meets(row[tag_col], row[ent_col])\n        if status is not None:\n            results.append(status)\n    if not results:\n        return None\n    return all(results)\n\n\ndf['meets'] = df.apply(row_meets, axis=1)\nsub = df[(df['year'] >= 2019) & (df['year'] <= 2023) & (df['meets'].notna())].copy()\n\n# Count total sampling dates and meeting dates per year, then average yearly meeting rates.\nyearly = sub.groupby('year')['meets'].agg(total='count', meeting='sum')\nyearly['rate'] = yearly['meeting'] / yearly['total']\n\noverall_percent = round(yearly['rate'].mean() * 100)\nprint(overall_percent)", "reason": "Rewrote the code to use the required local CSV path, robustly parse the datasheet structure, interpret Enterococcus results using '<' as non-violation and numeric values against the marine standard threshold (104), compute row-level compliance for 2019-2023, average the annual meeting rates, round to an integer percent, and print the result."}) [toolUseId=call_iG9UNsDmSuzgGiNnjqvBgeOJ]
